        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40452",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Could you explain where you see a problem?\r\n\r\nWhen a dialect does not have a translation then no output is returned.\r\nLists on the other hand are according to CLDR rules created by rerouting.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-12T11:11:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-12T11:11:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40455",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mverboeket",
                        "name": "mverboeket",
                        "displayName": "Micha Verboeket",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ok, but how to get e.g. \"Nederlands\" for country \"nl\" (localized translation for The Netherlands?\r\n\r\nI can image that \"false\" is returned if the dialect has no translation, but what is the interface then to get a localized translation for a country or language? It is inefficient to get the list and then filter the needed translation.\r\n\r\nAm I not aware of other interfaces \/ classes to do this? Or can this method\/class be enhanced with this functionality?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mverboeket",
                        "name": "mverboeket",
                        "displayName": "Micha Verboeket",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-12T11:41:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-12T11:41:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40456",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Normally you use the language instead of the fully qualified locale when you have only language informations unrelated from an region.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-12T12:11:09.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-12T12:11:09.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40457",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mverboeket",
                        "name": "mverboeket",
                        "displayName": "Micha Verboeket",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yes, but if the translations are available then why is there not an interface to it?\r\n\r\nAlso, in the following example the language \"nl\" is used instead of a specific locale\/dialect (like nl_BE) but it still returns \"false\":\r\n{code}Zend_Debug::dump(Zend_Locale::getTranslation('nl', 'country', 'nl'));{code}\r\n\r\nIf this is net yet available then I would suggest creating a new method for such functionality or maybe giving a parameter to the getTranslation() method to get the translation with some kind of \"fallback\" mechanism.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mverboeket",
                        "name": "mverboeket",
                        "displayName": "Micha Verboeket",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-12T12:29:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-12T12:29:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40458",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "There is an interface to it.\r\nUse the method \"getTranslation()\" properly.\r\n\r\nI see no problem on the interface.\r\n\r\nYou are requesting the language \"nl\" and expect it to be a country. Of course this returns \"false\" as a language is no country.\r\n\r\nSame for your first example.\r\nEven on this: Zend_Debug::dump(Zend_Locale::getTranslation('nl', 'country', 'en'));\r\nI get false because you are using language instead of country. Note: Doing such tests you should always disable the cache else you will have unexpected results.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-12T13:38:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-12T13:38:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40459",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mverboeket",
                        "name": "mverboeket",
                        "displayName": "Micha Verboeket",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ok maybe I can state it differently then. The country 'nl' would be \"The Netherlands\" or \"Nederland\" in Dutch. The language for 'nl' would be \"Dutch\" or \"Nederlands\".\r\n\r\nHow can I use Zend_Locale to get the localized\/translated country name, as the depricated method getCountryTranslation() should do if I am correct? My goals is to get country names translated, e.g. \"Nederland\" or \"Amerika\". How should the interface be used in this situation?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mverboeket",
                        "name": "mverboeket",
                        "displayName": "Micha Verboeket",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-12T13:47:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-12T13:47:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40460",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As you said:\r\n\r\n\"nl\" is the language. \"nl\" is not the country.\r\nLook at the output of getTranslationList... you will see that you have \"NL\" returned and not \"nl\".\r\nUsing full qualified locales you will also have \"nl_NL\" in return and not \"nl-nl\".\r\n\r\nSo to explain it once again as you did not understand:\r\ngetTranslation('nl', 'country', 'en') does not work.\r\n\r\nYou request the language \"nl\" but want it as detail from the country list using the language \"en\" as translation.\r\nThere is no language \"nl\" as a language is no country.\r\n\r\nYou can eighter call getTranslation('nl', 'language', 'en');\r\nto get a translation for the language \"nl\".\r\n\r\nOr you can call getTranslation('NL', 'territory', 'en');\r\nto get a translation for the territory\/country \"NL\".",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-12T14:12:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-12T14:12:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40461",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Closing as non-issue",
